---
Syntax: pick <container>
        pick <door keyword>

Attempts to pick the lock on a locked container or door using your
lockpicking skill. A successful pick unlocks the target without a key.
When picking a door, both sides of the door are unlocked simultaneously.

Success depends on your learned proficiency in the Pick Lock skill.
Higher skill levels give a better chance of success.

Restrictions:
  - The target must be closed, locked, and not pick-proof.
  - You cannot pick locks if a guard 5 or more levels above you is present
    in the room.
  - The item/door must be visible to you.

Example:
  pick chest          -- Attempts to pick the lock on a chest.
  pick north          -- Attempts to pick the lock on the north door.

See also: shelp pick lock open unlock close
